  "text": "Eight patients who completed the initial imaging studies within 6 hours received thrombolytic therapy. When they were excluded from the analysis, XeCT CBF and CTA were no longer predictive of infarction on outcome CT (Pϭ0. [CITATION_1] and Pϭ0.12). Conversely, XeCT CBF and CTA remained significantly predictive of discharge disposition in patients that did not have infarctions on their initial CT scans (Pϭ0.04 and Pϭ0.007). The NIHSS score continued to not be significantly predictive of either the follow-up CT (Pϭ0.60) or discharge disposition (Pϭ0.12).",
